<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100290228926578></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100290228926578><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2193&mid=100290228926578>Aegis of Life</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2193&mid=100290228926578#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=109555><span id= >Nylva</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 12th 11:58 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just obtained the Aegis of Life, and item stats aside, it was well worth getting this symbol of true dedication and merit.&nbsp;&nbsp;Everquest is not just about min-maxing your ability scores, but also about roleplaying your character.  Wear this item with pride.<br><br>Which (live or dead) version of Lord Grimrot will spawn, and at what IG hours you should kill the place-holder, is completely random.  The only thing certain is his spawn rate.<br><br>Word of advice: Keep killing those Putrid Skeletons while you wait on Lord Grimrot, and save all the bone chips that they drop.  You will not only improve faction with the Priests of Life when the skellies die, but you can also give the bone chips to Wolten Grafe (Paladin's Guild, South Qeynos) for more faction boosts.  I went from "indiferrent" to "ally" in two days, and it was worth ensuring that I get the quest.  (Keep in mind that the Corrupt Guards of Qeynos will not like you very much from then on).  Note, you do NOT have to be faction maxed to get the Aegis of Life, as some may have claimed in the past.<br>&nbsp;<br>Nylva Dominata<br>Priestess of Tunare<br>The Terris-Thule Server</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
