<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100230847020141></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100230847020141><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2193&mid=100230847020141>Don't believe all this mumbo-jumbo</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2193&mid=100230847020141#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=107531><span id= >TrylliumCalaquendi</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 5th 3:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The person who said:<br>"if you want a live pop kill the PH between 5-7pm, then exactly 3 hrs and 20 min later you will have a daytime pop of another PH or live grimrot.In order to get a dead grimrot kill the PH between 5-7 am you will have a nighttime pop of either a PH or undead grimrot"...<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; ...is blowing smoke, folks, this just can't be true.<br><br>Facts:<br>- An EQ day/night is 90 minutes long. Therefore, an hour in gametime is 3.75 real minutes long.<br>- Grimrot, or his PH, is on a spawn timer of 3 hours 10 minutes to 3 hours 20 minutes real time(I've been camping him for days now on Brell Serilis, and have been timing it carefully).<br>- 3 hrs 20 min realtime = 2 days, 5 1/3 hrs gametime.<br>- So, killing the PH at 5pm (for example) gives the next spawn at 10pm.  This ISN'T a "daytime pop" as described in the section I quoted from that other message...<br><br>My opinion, based on what I've seen?<br>The live version is more common than the undead one - I've yet to kill the undead and I've gotten the live one twice.<br>The PH or Grimrot spawns every 3 hrs 20 min, with perhaps 10 minutes variance maximum.<br>It's completely random what spawn you get.  I've tried the little tricks everyone has, and none of them have produced a spawn as described.<br><br>Just be patient and play an alt for the 3 hrs you're waiting... I will be very proud to wear the Aegis as the best back slot item I can reasonably obtain.<br><br>I salute you, clerics and paladins with the patience to do the quest.<br>&nbsp;<br>Tryllium Calaquendi<br>Resident Vicar, Sentinels of Veeshan<br>Brell Serilis</td></tr>
