	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK..this is how you do this quest..<br>1. If you kill the PH (a putrid skeli that is standing) at the 3AM hour you will get the Live Grimrot 3- 31/2 hrs later {real life time}..He is extremely magical resistant and has about 1800 hp (I scrolled and counted them)..He hits you with spells and weakens you. I'm a lvl 45 Pali and he conned blue to me..I killed him with lvl 28 shami buffs and one heal in 1 min. (had a wurmslayer attack of 860 and an ac of 950 and didn't get below 1/2 health..)<br>2. As for the dead grimrot i can't tell you yet, but the ph and spawn times are the same. I hear that the dead one is easier..I will post you soon..I hear you have to kill the ph at 3 pm to get the dead grimrot..<br>3. If you need faction the easiest way is to create a dummy monk, bind him in N.Qeynos by the pool where the pali is swimming {make sure you bind on the left side of the pool (the pali side)..make sure you put some pts in his fists..get a kick hot button and your rdy..Jump in and kill fish..After you've killed a fish or two make sure that there is a fish body in the loot..swim to the shore where your bound and log..<br>the fish spawn every 5 min or so and the carcus wont rot by the time you log on your player that needs the shield..Go and click on the fish and get the LORE fish body and give it to the swimming pali..make sure, make sure, make sure that you are amiable before you do this or else you won't any positive faction with him..Once you do this process 5-10 times I guarantee you'll go from amiable to Alli..that is how you get your faction (it will also help if you kill the skellis at the camp)<br>Im on the Hammer server if you have any questions<br>jsavorn 45th year Pali of the Pillars of Norath<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
