<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98900019031391></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98900019031391><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2193&mid=98900019031391>Faction with NIfe</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2193&mid=98900019031391#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 4th 2:16 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are having faction problems with this quest, as another poster has mentioned you can turn in 2gp to Novashine and get faction or you can give him bone chips (I don't remember how many at a time - I think 4).&nbsp;&nbsp;These will raise your faction, but slowly.<br><br>After getting faction to (I believe) amiably you are at a level where you can turn in Koalindl fish to the guard swimming in the Temple of Life pool.<br><br>Just as killing the fish in the pond is a MAJOR negative faction hit, turning one in is a MAJOR boost.  Check on this site on the legitimate ways of getting a fishy (regurgatonic or some nonsense).  Another simple, fast way is to create a new character in Qeynos (Wiz works well for me).  Have the new wizzy blast and stab fish in pond.  Do this at the end away from the swimming guard!  Check the body of the kofish.  If there is a nodrop fish on it log off with the mule and quickly log back on with your main character.  Loot the fish and give it to the swimming guard.  You get major faction and usually either a ring or prayer beads.  Keep the ring in the bank if you don't need to equip it -- that way if you repeat the quest you are most likely going to get the prayer beads (ring and beads are lore).  The beads have two charges of a nice healing spell.  After 6-7 repetitions of this your mule character will be KOS to most of the city.  Delete/recreate and start over.  Turning in fish will get you from amiably to kindly with almost no effort.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
