	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, here's the deal on faction.&nbsp;&nbsp;All these posts have said hail the guy in the temple and then say "I will defend life".  Supposedly, if your faction is high enough he will give you the quest.  Well, being a cleric of Rodcet Nife, I was already warmly as heck...that's right, I said heck.  He would never give me the quest.  So I worked on newbie quests for 2 full days.  I did so much gosh darn faction work that I recieved a full blue bubble of xp...and I'm lvl 54 if that says anything.  He still wouldn't give me the quest.  Finally irritated with the faction building I tried "I will defend life" again.  Still no quest given.  So I tried a different approach and asked "what about Lord Grimrot?"  Low and behold, he gives me a spill about a certain SK we all hate camping in SK.  After you read this new message you will see that the "I will defend life" is wrong.  After his new message say "I came here to defend life".  Zip bang...quest.  Hopefully this will end a lot of frustration that all you other paladins and clerics are having with the faction.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
